artnership among the member states could help protect the health and life of people in the region.\n\nMinister Gyawali had chaired the meeting. SAARC Secretary-General Esala Weerakoon said the SAARC Secretariat was committed to coordinating among the member states for recovery of the South Asian economy.\n\nRSS","title":"Nepal for activating SAARC economic mechanism - Khabarhub","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2020/16/128152/","video":[]}
